%interpolation lower end
%interpolation higher end

%higphass filter in hz (bandpass edge; cut-off frequency is different (for 1 Hz it is 0.5 Hz))
%lowpassfilter in hz (bandpass edge; Cut-off frequency is different)
%reduce linear trends (NOT recommendet for ERPs) 1 = yes; 0 = no
%0 = no notch filter (uses cleanline for line noise); 1 = IIR notch filter (-5 < frequency > +5 Hz)
%linenoise removal around hz
%start epoch in ms

%%if trial rejection automatic: rejection threshold in µV
%%0= nor re-referencing, 1 = avg reference, otherwise: it references to that channel (ex. FP1)
%%5=very strict, 30=very liberal, 19=good choice

%%1=plots data after every processing step, 0 = no plotting, if UiO_plot = 1 you should provide here at which state you want to plot your already saved data ('after_tms', 'preprocessed', 'after_pca', 'after_ica', 'ica_cleaned', 'after_inverse_model', 'after_pci')
%Do you want to switch channel locations? 0 = no; 1 = yes
% state the channels. First channel which should be replaced by the second channel (eg., AF8, FCz, AF7, Afz)
%Do you want to remove channels from analysis (EMG?)? 0 = no; state channels (eg. EMGh, EMGn) = otherwise
%%baseline length for inverse model and bootstraping
%%how much do you want to downsample the sources

%%how much downsample pci result in source domain (1: no downsampling, 2: every other
point, 3: every third etc)

%%how much downsample pci result in time domain (1: no downsampling, 2: every other
point, 3: every third etc)
%% length of the wavelet in seconds (should not be smaller than 1s; 2s is a good choice)
%% range of the frequency spectra (e.g. 2-100 decomposes data between 2 and 100 hz)
%% number of bins between lower and upper frequency edge (e.g. 40 would make 40 bins between 2 and 100 hz in logarithmic space)
%% number of lower and upper cycles (should not be lower than 3 and higher than 20). This changes logarithmic with frequency
%% wavelet function will compute the mean over the trials wich are stated here. Commata and hyphes are allowed (e.g. 1,2,3-5,10-20)
%% start time in ms for connectivity computation
%% end time in ms for connectivity computation
%% length of the baseline vector in the time domain in ms (e.g. 500ms)
%% starting point of the baseline vector in the dataset in ms (e.g. -1000ms would mean that 1000ms before movement start the baseline will be start and end after baseline_length)
%% option how frequency power is normalized. 1: percentage change (ERD/ERS), 2: decibel (db)
